00:10:07.000 Barcamp Science 2.0 #chapter

The Barcamp 2.0 is taking place on the 2nd of May 2016 in Cologne;
GESIS – Leibniz-Institute for the Social Sciences; <http://www.gesis.org/en/home/> #link
Barcamp Science 2.0 Topic: Putting Science 2.0 and Open Science into practice!;
The Barcamp addresses young researchers and in general all people interested in the open science practice;
Felix Schönbrodt from LMU Munich will provide the short talk in the beginning of the Barcamp;
Felix Schönbrodt; <http://www.nicebread.de/about/index.html> #link
Christian Heise has given the introductory talk last year; <http://christianheise.de/2015/03/the-bad-news-about-the-good-news-openness-has-won/> #link
Christian Heise; <http://christianheise.de/?cv=1> #link
Christian's open PhD thesis; <http://offene-doktorarbeit.de/> #link
LMU has published a job advert for a professorship with a clear statement to open science; <http://www.nicebread.de/open-science-hiring-practices/> #link
Sessions can already be proposed in the pad; <https://pad.okfn.org/p/s20bar_session_proposals> #link
Barcamp registration is still open; <https://www.eventbrite.com/e/barcamp-science-20-registration-23855480384> #link

00:22:46.000 Science 2.0 Conference #chapter

The Science 2.0 Conference is taking place on the 3rd and 4th of May 2016 in Cologne;
International Science 2.0 Conference and EEXCESS Final Conference; <https://www.science20-conference.eu/> #link
This year the topic is related to science policy and focuses on the European level and the European Open Science Agenda, specifically the European Open Science Cloud;
Open Science Agenda; <https://ec.europa.eu/digital-single-market/en/open-science> #link
European Open Science Cloud; <https://ec.europa.eu/research/openscience/index.cfm?pg=open-science-cloud> #link
High Level Expert Group for the European Open Science Cloud; <http://ec.europa.eu/transparency/regexpert/index.cfm?do=groupDetail.groupDetail&groupID=3353> #link
Registration for the Conference is also still open; <https://www.science20-conference.eu/registration/> #link
EEXCESS; <http://eexcess.eu/> #link
EEXCESS - What it's all about; <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5gy6V1M2R9M> #video
First Prototype tools are already available (such as browser plugins); <http://eexcess.eu/results/> #link
Programme of the conference; <https://www.science20-conference.eu/programme/> #link

